Discrete model

Plots

dat_arousal_long = dat %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = c(dplyr::ends_with("_post")),
               names_to = "emot_type",
               values_to = "emot_value") %>% 
  dplyr::filter(emot_type %in% c("excitation_post", "valence_post"))


ggplot(dat_arousal_long, 
       aes(x = Valence, y = emot_value, fill = emot_type)) +

dat_emot_long = dat %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = c(dplyr::ends_with("_dif")),
               names_to = "emot_type",

Post-hoc + adjusted SMD

post_hoc_films = emmeans(mlm_films, 
                         trt.vs.ctrlk ~ Valence | list_emots, 
                         mult.name = "list_emots", adjust = "none")
res_films = data.frame(test(post_hoc_films, 
                       adjust = "none")$contrasts)
dat_sd = dat %>% 
         group_by(Valence) %>%
         summarise(
             n = n(),
             sd_joy = sd(joy_post),
             sd_amusemennt = sd(amusement_post),
             sd_fear = sd(fear_post),
             sd_sadness = sd(sadness_post),
             sd_disgust = sd(disgust_post),
             sd_anger = sd(anger_post))
dat_em = data.frame(post_hoc_films$emmeans)
dat_smd_raw = dplyr::left_join(dat_em, dat_sd)
## Joining, by = "Valence"
dat_joy_sad = subset(dat_smd_raw, Valence != "Neutral")
dat_neut = subset(dat_smd_raw, Valence == "Neutral")
colnames(dat_neut) = paste0(colnames(dat_neut), "_neut")
dat_neut$list_emots = dat_neut$list_emots_neut
dat_smd = dplyr::left_join(dat_joy_sad, dat_neut)
## Joining, by = "list_emots"
dat_smd$sd_1 = with(dat_smd,
  ifelse(list_emots=="fear_post", sd_fear,
         ifelse(list_emots=="anger_post", sd_anger,
                ifelse(list_emots=="disgust_post", sd_disgust,
                       ifelse(list_emots=="amusement_post", sd_amusemennt,
                              ifelse(list_emots=="joy_post", sd_joy,
                                     ifelse(list_emots=="sadness_post", sd_sadness, NA)))))))
dat_smd$sd_2 = with(dat_smd,
  ifelse(list_emots=="fear_post", sd_fear_neut,
         ifelse(list_emots=="anger_post", sd_anger_neut,
                ifelse(list_emots=="disgust_post", sd_disgust_neut,
                       ifelse(list_emots=="amusement_post", sd_amusemennt_neut,
                              ifelse(list_emots=="joy_post", sd_joy_neut,
                                     ifelse(list_emots=="sadness_post", sd_sadness_neut, NA)))))))

       
es = compute.es::mes(m.1=dat_smd$emmean, m.2=dat_smd$emmean_neut, 
         sd.1=dat_smd$sd_1, sd.2=dat_smd$sd_2, 
         n.1=dat_smd$n, n.2=dat_smd$n_neut, verbose = FALSE)
res_films$smd = es$d
res_films$smd_lo = es$l.d
res_films$smd_up = es$u.d

post_hoc_films = emmeans(mlm_films, 
                         trt.vs.ctrlk ~ Valence | list_emots, 
                         mult.name = "list_emots", adjust = "none")
res_films = data.frame(test(post_hoc_films, 
                       adjust = "none")$contrasts)
dat_sd = dat %>% 
         group_by(Valence) %>%
         summarise(
             n = n(),
             sd_valence = sd(valence_post),
             sd_excitation= sd(excitation_post))
dat_em = data.frame(post_hoc_films$emmeans)
dat_smd_raw = dplyr::left_join(dat_em, dat_sd)
## Joining, by = "Valence"
dat_joy_sad = subset(dat_smd_raw, Valence != "Neutral")
dat_neut = subset(dat_smd_raw, Valence == "Neutral")
colnames(dat_neut) = paste0(colnames(dat_neut), "_neut")
dat_neut$list_emots = dat_neut$list_emots_neut
dat_smd = dplyr::left_join(dat_joy_sad, dat_neut)
## Joining, by = "list_emots"
dat_smd$sd_1 = ifelse(dat_smd$list_emots=="valence_post", 
                      dat_smd$sd_valence, 
                      dat_smd$sd_excitation)
dat_smd$sd_2 = ifelse(dat_smd$list_emots=="valence_post", 
                      dat_smd$sd_valence_neut,
                      dat_smd$sd_excitation_neut)

         sd.1=dat_smd$sd_1, sd.2=dat_smd$sd_2, 
         n.1=dat_smd$n, n.2=dat_smd$n_neut, verbose = FALSE)

Logistic regression

dat$Framing = factor(dat$Framing)
dat$excitation_post = as.numeric(dat$excitation_post)
glm_framing = glm(risky_choice ~ excitation_post * Framing,
                  data = dat,
                  family = "binomial",
                  contrasts=list(Framing=contr.sum))

car::Anova(glm_framing)
## Analysis of Deviance Table (Type II tests)
## 
## Response: risky_choice
##                         LR Chisq Df Pr(>Chisq)    
## excitation_post           0.8554  1    0.35502    
## Framing                  20.9642  1   4.68e-06 ***
## excitation_post:Framing   3.1907  1    0.07406 .  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
test(emtrends(glm_framing, ~Framing, var = "excitation_post",
              type = "response"), adjust = "bonferroni")
##  Framing excitation_post.trend    SE  df z.ratio p.value
##  Gain                   -0.137 0.183 Inf  -0.749  0.9072
##  Loss                    0.292 0.159 Inf   1.837  0.1324
## 
## P value adjustment: bonferroni method for 2 tests
confint(emtrends(glm_framing, ~Framing, var = "excitation_post",
              type = "response"), adjust = "bonferroni")
##  Framing excitation_post.trend    SE  df asymp.LCL asymp.UCL
##  Gain                   -0.137 0.183 Inf   -0.5468     0.273
##  Loss                    0.292 0.159 Inf   -0.0642     0.647
## 
## Confidence level used: 0.95 
## Conf-level adjustment: bonferroni method for 2 estimates
interactions::johnson_neyman(
  model = glm(risky_choice ~ excitation_post * FramingNum,
              data = dat, family = "binomial"), 
  pred = FramingNum, modx = excitation_post, mod.range = c(1, 5))
## JOHNSON-NEYMAN INTERVAL 
## 
## When excitation_post is INSIDE the interval [1.83, 27.88], the slope of
## FramingNum is p < .05.
## 
## Note: The range of observed values of excitation_post is [1.00, 5.00]

Linear regression

lm_em_arousal = lm(emot_risky_choice ~ Framing * excitation_post,
              data = dat,
              contrasts=list(
                Framing=contr.sum))
car::Anova(lm_em_arousal, type = "III")
## Anova Table (Type III tests)
## 
## Response: emot_risky_choice
##                          Sum Sq  Df F value   Pr(>F)

## Residuals               272.074 236                    
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
test(emtrends(lm_em_arousal, ~Framing, var = "excitation_post"), adjust = "bonferroni")
